Amazon.com Issues Q1 2012 Guidance; Earnings Guidance Below Analysts' Estimates

Tuesday, 31 Jan 2012 04:01pm EST

Amazon.com announced that for the first quarter of 2012, it expects net sales to be between $12.0 billion and $13.4 billion, or to grow between 22% and 36% compared with first quarter of 2011. Operating income (loss) is expected to be between $(200) million and $100 million, or between 162% decline and 69% decline compared with first quarter of 2011. According to I/B/E/S Estimates, analysts on an average are expecting the Company to report revenue of $13.4 billion and operating profit of $226.84 million for the first quarter of 2012.Â 

